10_graph_inverse


  1. Question

    The one-to-one function \(f\) is plotted below:


    Which of the following red curves is a graph of the inverse function, \(f^{-1}\)?

    • A

    • B

    • C

    • D


    1. A
    2. B
    3. C
    4. D

    Solution

    The correct answer should have reflective symmetry across the \(y=x\) line, also known as the 45\(^\circ\) line.

    So, the correct answer is D:
